    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Diospyros digyna, native to eastern Mexico, Central America, and south to Colombia. The wood is yellowish to deep-yellow with black markings near the heart of old trunks; it is compact and suitable for cabinetwork. Reports of dark wood utilized for furniture are probably the result of confusion with other species of the genus Diospyros.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
